def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)
    
    if axis == 1:
        if key in obj.columns:
            keys = [obj.columns.get_loc(key)]
        elif is_list_like(key):
            keys = [obj.columns.get_loc(k) for k in key if k in obj.columns]
        else:
            raise KeyError(key)
    else:
        keys = [key]

    groupings = [
        Grouping(
            group_axis,
            gpr,
            obj=obj,
            sort=sort,
            observed=observed,
            in_axis=True
        ) for gpr in keys
    ]

    # Create the internals grouper
    grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
    return grouper, [], obj
